## v1.1.0 (2026-05-28)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus issue #539 verify-and-close session
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed

- Added "Verify-and-close" trigger to description and When to Use
- Added `── VERIFY-AND-CLOSE ──` Quick Reference block in Verified Workflow
- Added 1 new Failed Attempts row: "Concluding already resolved from keyword presence without grep"
- Added 1 new Verified On row: ProjectHephaestus issue #539

### Why

Documented the pattern of independently verifying an issue is already resolved using
`grep -rn` with exit-code evidence, then posting a structured comment and closing with
`gh issue close --reason completed`. This is faster and safer than implementation when
the preliminary checks strongly suggest the fix is already in place.

